data.description:
BEST BUY IN NORTH AURORA REDUCED $55,000. Beautiful evening sunsets await you from the backyard patio overlooking the pond.  One of only 11 homes on the pond in the Orchard Crossing subdivision. In addition this home has an easement next door so you will never have a neighbor on both sides of you making for lots of privacy. Tuscan model features 4 bedrooms and 2.5 baths with 2500 sq feet of living space on 2 floors plus a full basement. Hardwood floors in foyer, dining room and family room. Kitchen features ceramic tile floor, large table area, breakfast bar, island, pantry closet and tile backsplash. All kitchen appliances remain as does the washer and dryer in the 1st floor laundry/mud room. Upstairs is 4 bedrooms. The master suite has a large walk-in closet and private bath with 2 bowl vanity, separate shower and tub. The Orchard Crossing subdivision has its own grade (Fearn) and middle (Jewel ) school, both within close walking distance to the home. There are lighted baseball and soccer fields, play grounds and parks within the subdivision. Orchard Crossing is convenient to I88 access or Randall Rd. Shopping and restaurants abound. Metra train station in Aurora is less than 15 minutes away.

Neighborhood Description

There are only 150 home in the subdivision and 11 of the homes have premium waterfront lots like this home. There is a grade school and middle school in the center of the subdivision within walking distance for all homes. There is a lighted baseball field, soccer field, play ground and park for all the residents to use. Commuting is easy as access to Interstate I88 is less than 1 mile away. Shopping, restaurants and other retail stores are all around. The Metra train station is only 15 minutes away. A wonderful place to live.
